  "texts": [
    "The datasets vary in graph sizes, ranging from small-scale graphs with thousands of nodes and edges (e.g., UCI [82] and Contact [81]) to large-scale graphs with millions or even billions of nodes (e.g., Taobao [87,88] and MAG [74]).",
    "This indicates that existing datasets can support research and applications at different scales.",
    "Many datasets are bipartite graphs.",
    "For example, datasets such as MOOC [54], LastFM [54], eBay [86],and TaoBao [86] fall into this category, with nodes categorized into two distinct sets and edges representing interactions between these sets.",
    "In contrast, some datasets, like Enron [80] and SocialEvo [100], are general graphs."
  ],
